among logicians, one of the modes of the <a class="xref" href="vol0.html#article-SECOND">second</a> <a class="xref" href="vol0.html#article-FIGURE">figure</a> of syllogisms; the <a class="xref" href="vol0.html#article-MINOR">minor</a> proposition of which is an <a class="xref" href="vol20.html#article-UNIVERSAL">universal</a> affirmative, and the other two universal negatives: thus,

CE <a class="xref" href="../1842/vol0.html#article-NO">No</a> immoral books ought to be read;
SA But every obscene book is immoral;
RE Therefore no obscene books ought to be read.
